 def fib(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    else:
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)

This function calculates the Fibonacci sequence for each given number using recursion. It starts from the base case where if the input is less than or equal to 1, it simply returns the number itself (either 0 or 1 in this case). For any other case, it calls itself recursively twice to calculate the values of two previous numbers and then adds them together.

